ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Attend all sessions because despite the fact that you don't learn anything you will be penalized for not going.
overall it was fine and i think it has the potential to be very helpful for some students
It's a course that teaches you some useful skills for research. I strongly recommend this course to the fellow students, for this course is very practical and useful.
CBIO 900 is a course more to help answer question on how graduate schools works and the fine details on how the writing process of papers is, possibilities after graduation, and graduate school life.
This is a required course that covers general research skills.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: The GRFP reviews were very helpful. That was one class of about a dozen.
various topics were introduced and it was helpful to have some information on ones such as grant writing.
I learned how to present my research and to utilize multiple resources for research, which is very helpful for my future research.
It deffinatly made me feel more prepared on what is required of me during my graduate school. It also gave me a good idea on how the life and process of becoming a professor is like.
It helped me by providing specifics for the NSF-GRFP grant proposal we all did earlier this year.
